tip.text: News report" enforcement personnel found carcass of a rat inside d kitchen.At least 10 stainless steel bowls, used to prepare the steamed glutinous rice or "loh mai kai", were filled with tiny worms
Very rich bah kut teh soup. Offal cuts are fresh , meat is very tender . Ya char kwai is soft .
I vote this the best tong sui on the street. Sweeter , bigger portion , costs a bit more .

venue.name: Gan En Wu Tang Shui Enterprise (Gan En Wu Tang Shui Enterprise 感恩屋糖水)

tip.text: Mixed roast pork is good !
Local secret . Very pleasant and reasonably priced Duck Egg Char Koay Teow . No crazy crowds to fight for table space with , this man has been frying since his Dad's time in this very same kopitiam

venue.name: City Rio Cafe 新麗羅茶室

tip.text: The yee sang this year is a bigger portion but it lacked one flavour ...sweetness , and ended up soggy and sour . Please buck up next year .
They are Hakkas but this is just food. Not Malaysian hawker level but an experimental housewife's stage. The good : fresh meats n fish
1. When the infamous aunty is not frying she's behind the cash counter 2. $12 gets you 4 or 5 large prawns  3. She's Thai Chinese
Love the nasi lemak with mint chicken curry ! Get your fav fishballs from the side stand
Save your airfare to Hong Kong. This makes the cut ! Nowadays it is so hard to find great braised beef brisket n tendon even in HK . FANTASTIC sheer fine springy noodles ! Good , friendly service
Look at the changing signboard for specials n offers during weekdays and certain times . Very nice n crisp Louisiana rub wings . Cajun wings can match Chilis buffalo wings in level of addictiveness
Cheap n foreigner friendly South Indian cuisine place in little india. Endless line of workers doing takeaways . Tasty but extremely spicy chicken curry and delicious vegie dishes too !
I really dont understand d queue,crowd, big fuss over this place.Half boiled egg is not fresh,toast bread is multigrain,kaya is ok only, tea and coffee r weak .Thank god we didn't try d mains

tip.text: Checkers cake gets my vote. There's also a flourless cake that has plenty of chocolatey goodness inside
Soy sauce based items r slightly on d sweet side. Pig organ soup is very fresh & excellent. White rice is superb ! Do get the lemonade drink . Combined with soup , leaves a sweet milky aftertaste .

venue.name: Authentic Mun Chee Kee KING of Pig's Organ Soup

tip.text: Local secret. Super long basmati rice. Lightly fragrant n moist. Try to get the mutton with bone , the meat just pulls away nicely , very tender , very sedap !

Staff is always full of smiles, helpful and friendly . You can walk to the scenic river at the back or straight into the shopping street with a Rewe at the end.Train gives you quick access 2 Frankfurt
Compared to the oldish rooms , treat yourself to a sit down meal at Novo2 . Service is surprisingly classy in a restaurant full of vibe. Menu is given a chic twist . Must try !
I am sooooo impressed ! The rooms are beautiful , sink into the fluffy pillows and duvet . Love how they maxed out a small space and squeezed a bathroom in the middle . Cleaners work amazing fast !
Staff are unobtrusive, hardworking. Breakfast is not bad , you even have herring + hard boiled egg ( one guest told us that this is a typical German breakfast ). Open till late. Very cozy .
Hang onto your ticket from beginning to end or you will have difficulty getting out . There's a restaurant option at the top .Elevator gives you a view of the lift shaft at top speed

Go up to the extensive food floor just below the expensive foodcourt . When they say they sell everything , this is what they mean.Do not miss seeing the moving window displays after dark.Super cute !
D owner loves to prank customers . Big hearted fella with huge sense of humour . Lamb shank was ok . Electric piano player really loves to sing haha very entertaining
You have to pay 3 euros for a photo or the boys might yell at ya . Mc D's toilet charges 0.50 euros to use the loo. Souvenier shop has a wall sticker of the original post. Worth a look
Hitler married Eva Braun in the underground bunkers , committed suicide there , instructed for his body to be burnt in the open.Covered and sealed to prevent Neo Nazis setting up a worship shrine
Everyone else lose. Their kimchi soup is the best ! Authentic and fresh Kimchi !!! Sooooooo delicious lorrrr !!!!
Superior stock , high quality hand picked ingredients go into every single dish that they make. Clam pan mee has delicious wine inside . Other items ...Salmon skin, deep fried enoki , bacon pan mee !

tip.text: Wall with bottles of wine belong to individual regular customers who dine here. Prices range from $40 to $400. I don't like the noodles. But the wine and bursting meatball is quite good .

venue.name: Go Noodles House 有間麵館

tip.text: The revamped airport is world class . Lots of space , all the branded goods you ever needed and more .  Seek the many giant structures scattered around , with the monorail , feels like a theme park
Clear your plates or the young lady will throw a tantrum. The curry is very fragrant. Worth a try
Wonderful place. They make sure that there are not too many people inside so that everyone is comfortable . Just there is no hairdryer in the shower room .
Very good white tomyam noodles . Fried garoupa done fish and chips style .
Try the new Fish Fest menu ! Penang has 2 outlets out of 3 in the whole country to offer it. Salmon is fresh and yummy.

Original southern fried chicken is anytime better than Mc D . For those who miss Shake Shack's ( in New York ) custard milkshake , get the vanilla ice cream cone ...just as good.Burger patties 2 thin.
Formerly from Abu Koyah road been open for 2 years.Very polite . Real mamak food we r used to. No rohingya no bangla no afghan cooks thank gawds.Maggi soup, fried egg, fried chicken good
I wouldn't say this is an American restaurant . The fusion of tastes are fantastic combo of the best of Australian and Malaysian . SUPERB cooking . You beat every hotel chef hands down !
Very good , tasty and fresh chia hu / chiam hui / whiting fish . Must eat ! Unlike Penang deep fried style , here , the fish body is soft and oily
Nice individual mini pavilions for massage . Try to take a longer bath / soak session . For those who are shy about people looking at their naked bodies , the masseurs here respect that & understand
Nasi padang Indonesian style that is very cheap . When you sit they serve you a bowl of desserts.
Dumplings , beef soup
Aglio olio very yummy. Mushroom soup very filling.Smoked ham burger looks great.
